    "To answer this question, we develop a semi-analytical procedure to predict the detectability of the different HMs over the fundamental mode (2, 2).",
    "These techniques have been first introduced in the context of TGRs to study the detection of GR deviations in the high SNR limit [144,163,164].In general, we define the time-domain scalar product weighted with the inverse autocovariance matrix asa|b ≡ a T C -1 nn b,(8)where a and b are two time series, and C nn is the autocovariance matrix of the detector noise.",
